<p>I am trying to add a meta-box to the woo commerce order details page. I've added the user role and made a dropdown menu to pull the users from that dropdown. that works fine, but now I need to be able to save the data and I also plan on being able to export this data with the rest of the order details. the cod</p>  <p>Here's the code I need help with       <pre><code>function add_courier_meta_boxes() { add_meta_box(      'woocommerce-courier',      __( 'Courier' ),      'courier_meta',      'shop_order',      'side',      'default'  ); } function courier_meta() { global $post;  //get users by role echo '&lt;input type="hidden" name="couriermeta_noncename" id="couriermeta_noncename" value="' .  wp_create_nonce( plugin_basename(__FILE__) ) . '" /&gt;'; $user = get_post_meta($post-&gt;ID, '_user', true); args1 = array (  'role' =&gt; 'courier',  'orderby' =&gt; 'user_nicename',  'order' =&gt; 'ASC' );  $couriers = get_users($args1); echo '&lt;select names= Name&gt;'; foreach ($couriers as $user) { echo '&lt;option name="_user" value="' . $user-&gt;display_name  . '"&gt;' . $user-&gt;display_name.'&lt;/option&gt;'; } echo '&lt;/select&gt;'; } // this section of code is suppose to save whats selected in the dropbox  function save_courier_meta($post_id, $post ){ if (!wp_verify_nonce( $_POST['couriermeta_noncename'], plugin_basename(__FILE__) )) return $post-&gt;ID; }  if ( !current_user_can( 'edit_post', $post-&gt;ID )) return $post-&gt;ID;  $courier_meta['_user'] = $_POST['_user'];  foreach ($courier_meta as $key =&gt; $value){ if ( $post-&gt;post_type == 'revision') return;} $value = implode(',', (array)$value); if (get_post_meta($post-&gt;ID, $key, FALSE)){ update_post_meta($_post-&gt;ID, $key, $value);  }else { add_post_meta($post-&gt;ID, $key, $value); } if(!$value) delete_post_meta($post-&gt;ID, $key);  add_action('save_post', 'save_courier_meta', 1, 2);  </code></pre>